Name: Canada Pond Management Area
Remarks: Former mill pond; includes a dam

Name: Memorial Park
Remarks: World War I Memorial; other sculpture

Name: Obediah Brown Fields
Remarks: One field is leased to RI College

Name: Pleasant Valley Pkwy
Remarks: Grass median strip with small stream

Name: Prete-Metcalf Field
Remarks: Arthur E. Coia Memorial Walking Trail

Name: St. John's Park
Remarks: Former location of St. John's Church

Name: Chocolate Mill Overlook
Remarks: Chocolate Mill Overlook is a park located on the banks of the Blackstone River in Central Falls, Rhode Island that celebrates one of North America's earliest water-powered chocolate mills.

Name: Coutu Memorial Park
Remarks: The Coutu Memorial Park is dedicated to Chief Robert A. Coutu and Chief René R. Coutu of the Central Falls Fire Department to recognize their numerous contributions to the city and their department.

Name: Crossman Street Playground
Remarks: This one-acre park has a tot lot, playground equipment and a walk through from Crossman Street to Earle Street as well as parking for twelve vehicles.

Name: Dexter Plaza
Remarks: Before, this site was an abandoned house. Then a vacant lot. Today, it's a beautiful brick-terraced plaza, complete with stage, shade pavilion, and mural made from tile contributions of the community. Thanks to the incredible work of RISD Desine Lab, Javeriana University, and the city of Central Falls, RI!

Name: Garfield Street Playground
Remarks: This 1/4-acre playground is used heavily all year and is home to our recreational summer camp from June through August.

Name: Higginson Avenue/Francis Corrigan Sports Complex
Remarks: This 8.3 acre multi-sport complex features a baseball field, two basketball courts, a football field,a soccer field and a 3/4-mile track. The facility is used from April through October for various sports.

Name: Illinois Street Playground
Remarks: This facility is undergoing a renovation and total redesign in 2016.

Name: Macomber Stadium
Remarks: Home to the Central Falls High School football, soccer, baseball and softball teams, this multi-sport complex is used from April through November for various sports.

Name: Pierce Park
Remarks: This site, home to en epic battle between colonialists and Native Americans, is now a riverfront part with both active and passive recreation, benches and a 1/4-mile trail along the historic Blackstone River.

Name: River Island Park & Campground
Remarks: This 2.5-acre park features an 1/8-mile walking track with a foot bridge crossing over to the Blackstone River and offers scenic and passive recreation.

Name: Sacred Heart Ave. Playground
Remarks: This one-acre playground has a tot lot, playground equipment and an intensely-used basketball court, along with parking for twenty vehicles.

Name: Saul Tarlow/High Street Ballfield
Remarks: Home to the Central Falls Little League, this baseball field also has a concession  stand and is open from April through July.
